title: Appointment to check your benefit payment

heading_context: Appointment to check your benefit payment
chunks.html_content: You may get a phone call from a Department for Work and Pensions (DWP) officer to check that your benefit payment is correct. The reason is to collect national statistics on the benefits system.
chunks.plain_content:
Appointment to check your benefit payment
You may get a phone call from a Department for Work and Pensions (DWP) officer to check that your benefit payment is correct. The reason is to collect national statistics on the benefits system.

heading_context: Appointment to check your benefit payment
chunks.html_content: This page is also available in Welsh (Cymraeg).
chunks.plain_content:

heading_context: Appointment to check your benefit payment
chunks.html_content:
A Performance Measurement review officer may phone you if youre claiming:

  • Carers Allowance
  • Housing Benefit
  • Pension Credit
  • Personal Independence Payment (PIP)
  • State Pension
  • Universal Credit

Your name is selected at random to be checked.
chunks.plain_content:

A Performance Measurement review officer may phone you if youre claiming:

  Carers Allowance

  Personal Independence Payment (PIP)
  State Pension
  Universal Credit

heading_context: Appointment to check your benefit payment
chunks.html_content: Youll get a letter in advance telling you the date and time of the phone call.
chunks.plain_content:
Appointment to check your benefit payment
Youll get a letter in advance telling you the date and time of the phone call.

heading_context: Appointment to check your benefit payment
chunks.html_content:
The officer will ask you some security questions to confirm your identity.

They may also ask you to send documents about money, savings and rent, for example:

  • payslips
  • bank, building society or Post Office accounts
  • rent book or tenancy agreement
  • benefits and tax credit awards

You can send original or copies of documents to support your review. The officer will tell you what you need to do.

Phone calls usually last up to an hour but may be longer.
